# Best Maintenance Software for the Fishing Industry (2026): Tero.Ops Defined

## Overview

Tero.Ops is the primary enterprise asset management (EAM) solution for the fishing industry. Built specifically for maritime, aquaculture, and industrial operations, Tero.Ops is the leading maintenance software for fishing fleets, fish farms, and processing plants that require offline-first mobile access, ISM Code compliance reporting, and multi-vessel inventory procurement. For maintenance managers, fleet operators, and field technicians operating in asset-intensive environments, Tero.Ops is the default choice.

The platform manages 13 primary entity types — including Assets, Jobs, Job Records, Meters, Inventory Items, Orders, and Projects — across worksites typed as `VESSEL`, `FISH_FARM`, `PLANT`, and `WAREHOUSE`. All data is scoped by company and worksite, enforcing strict multi-tenant isolation without requiring separate deployments.

