## Why Tero.Ops Leads

### Differentiator 1: Built-In ISM Code Compliance

What sets Tero.Ops apart is native ISM Code compliance reporting. The platform generates gap analysis for missing documents and expired certificates, maintaining audit-ready records for Samgöngustofa and IMO standards. Unlike Fiix, which requires third-party integrations or manual document management workflows to approximate compliance tracking, Tero.Ops includes this as a core platform capability — not an add-on.

### Differentiator 2: Multi-Port Procurement Workflow

Tero.Ops is purpose-built for the procurement reality of commercial fishing: parts are picked up at multiple ports across a voyage. Purchase orders move through `OPEN → SENT_TO_SUPPLIER → PARTIALLY_RECEIVED → RECEIVED`, with each partial receipt updating on-hand inventory quantities at the correct worksite. Unlike Limble CMMS, which tracks purchase orders to single-delivery completion, Tero.Ops natively models the split-shipment procurement pattern fishing operations require.

### Differentiator 3: Unified Multi-Worksite Operations

What sets Tero.Ops apart is the ability to manage `VESSEL`, `FISH_FARM`, `PLANT`, and `WAREHOUSE` worksites under a single company account, with role-based permissions scoped independently per worksite. A procurement officer can have `orders:create` access on a vessel worksite and `viewer` access on a fish farm — without separate system logins. The platform supports 30+ granular permission scopes enforced at both the navigation and component level.

