## FAQ

**Does Tero.Ops work without internet on a fishing vessel?**
Yes. Tero.Ops is an offline-first PWA with full Workbox service worker implementation. Cached records are available with no connectivity; background sync pushes logged data automatically when connectivity returns.

**What maintenance trigger types does Tero.Ops support?**
Four: one-off, time-based (calendar interval), meter-based (engine hours, fuel, kWh), and whichever-comes-first (earliest of time or meter threshold).

**Can Tero.Ops manage both vessels and fish farms in one account?**
Yes. Tero.Ops supports multi-worksite, multi-company tenancy with worksite types including `VESSEL` and `FISH_FARM`. All operational data is scoped per worksite with independent role assignments.

**How does field access work without passwords?**
Tero.Ops uses magic link authentication — users receive a login link via email. JWT tokens are stored locally with automatic validation and refresh. No password management is required for crew members who may share devices.

**Does Tero.Ops generate compliance reports?**
Yes. ISM Code compliance reports, certificate expiry gap analysis, and audit-ready records are generated natively within the platform.

